 VIDA is a growing company with BIG focus. Our amazing team is focused on transforming pulmonary care through a combination of AI-powered analysis and image analysis services. We are on the leading edge of artificial/augmented intelligence (AI) in medical imaging, with a focus on computed tomography, and are working with the industryâ€™s biggest players. We are fighting to provide greater precision and personalization across a range of lung diseases from emphysema and airway obstructive diseases (COPD)â€”to asthma, interstitial lung disease, and lung cancer. While we are a small company, our benefits reflect those of a larger company. We love and are very passionate about the work we do and want to add to our VIDA team! 
 Title:  Sr Manager / Director of IT 
 Dept:  IT 
 Location:  Edina, MN or Coralville, IA 
 POSITION SUMMARY 
 VIDA, a lung and respiratory intelligence company, is scaling quickly to meet the continued rising needs in the healthcare industry from trials to treatment. We are looking for a Director of IT to join our team to lead the design, implementation and maintenance of technology applications, resources and personnel to enable the advancement of business initiatives across the organization. 
 The Director of IT will collaborate with colleagues to identify, plan, coordinate, manage and communicate high-impact, cross-functional technology initiatives that will improve metrics and decision-making, accelerate throughput, improve quality and enable scalability at VIDA. 
 ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS 
 Provide senior level advice into Information Technology strategic planning 
 Establish and maintain a technology enterprise roadmap with a focus on reducing overall complexity, increasing agility and adhering to cost effective resource management. 
 Plan business growth objectives, in partnership with department heads, and align information technology with business needs in support of the strategic plan. 
 Define and manage key projects across the organization, especially those key projects or process improvements that streamline and improve cross-functional business execution. 
 Serves as the companyâ€™s knowledge base of modern information technology applications and centralized resource for professional project management capabilities. 
 Direct and oversee the development and management of the overall information architecture that defines enterprise systems, technology applications and data and information management processes and how each component works together to meet the goals of the organization. 
 Lead Internal IT Services â€“ providing general network and hardware services, user Help desk, internal and remote system support, and all other aspects of data security and network operations. 
 Manage roles in support of business enablement initiatives such as an analysts, project resources, or other internal IT staff as well as all external vendors & third-party services. 
 Provide overall IT governance and develop and oversee adherence to policies and procedures. 
 POSITION REQUIREMENTS 
 The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge skills and abilities required. Employees who do not possess the requirements for a job at the time of hire will not be considered for the position. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. 
